Bow? What for?

12
00:01:46,906 --> 00:01:49,136
Because you're here
for the first time.

13
00:01:49,743 --> 00:01:51,370
This is the threshhold
of your house.

14
00:01:52,178 --> 00:01:55,147
Won't just folding my hands do?
The ground must be very hot.

15
00:01:56,249 --> 00:01:58,945
Okay, okay, don't look like that.

16
00:02:03,256 --> 00:02:05,554
l said, bow to it.

17
00:02:15,135 --> 00:02:18,468
Sit down, sit down. There is no escape
from this.

18
00:02:23,543 --> 00:02:25,443
You used to pine for this desert
out there?

19
00:02:25,912 --> 00:02:27,880
This is not just a desert.

20
00:02:28,114 --> 00:02:31,515
Just look around, it's full
of your family's legends

21
00:02:32,085 --> 00:02:36,988
Legends don't have to bear the heat.
Else, they'd get a sun-stroke too!

22
00:02:37,924 --> 00:02:39,221
Keep quiet.

23
00:02:40,093 --> 00:02:45,190
Just see, they are sitting as though
this desert is air-conditioned!

24
00:02:45,698 --> 00:02:47,666
What stuff are these
people made of?

25
00:02:47,967 --> 00:02:49,935
They are made out of
the local soil.

26
00:02:50,236 --> 00:02:53,603
They're as seasoned as
the tree above them.

27
00:02:55,241 --> 00:02:59,541
Papa migrated before
l was born, else...

28
00:03:04,417 --> 00:03:07,215
When this sun seasons you too
in a couple of days,...

29
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:11,479
and when it narrates to you the
unlimited legends of your ancestors...

30
00:03:11,758 --> 00:03:13,487
you too will be happy.

31
00:03:15,795 --> 00:03:17,126
After signing the papers,...

32
00:03:17,263 --> 00:03:20,232
l'll catch the first flight
to London.

33
00:03:20,767 --> 00:03:22,735
As you command.

34
00:03:23,336 --> 00:03:26,499
Don't use that tone with me, please.
l feel as though you're scolding me!

35
00:03:26,806 --> 00:03:28,774
l am scolding you!

36
00:03:28,942 --> 00:03:34,903
Okay, l'll do my work,
bow to the land...

37
00:03:35,281 --> 00:03:38,250
seek your permission,
then go away. Happy?

38
00:03:39,752 --> 00:03:41,720
Forget all that for now.

39
00:03:42,088 --> 00:03:46,650
Your talk has moved the
mansion itself to hug you!

40
00:03:58,638 --> 00:04:06,340
Greetings - Greetings - Greetings
- Greetings - Come, Let's go.

41
00:04:21,227 --> 00:04:23,195
His Lordship has
certainly grown up!

42
00:04:23,596 --> 00:04:27,088
This is the caretaker
of this place. Mr. Tiwari.

43
00:04:30,069 --> 00:04:33,698
What's all this farce?
- Tradition, son.

44
00:04:34,641 --> 00:04:40,307
Your father went abroad, but your
parents' portraits hang here.

45
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:42,648
Parents don't have feet,
you see...

46
00:04:44,517 --> 00:04:46,485
Can l remove this garland now?

47
00:04:49,756 --> 00:04:52,247
Our neighbour, Mr. Thakur is here. -Okay.

48
00:04:52,792 --> 00:04:54,760
Who is he?

49
00:04:55,361 --> 00:05:00,890
He's not just a neighbour, but
a very good friend of your father.

50
00:05:01,367 --> 00:05:05,895
When the world had deserted him,
this man stood firmly by him.

51
00:05:06,506 --> 00:05:09,202
Don't just greet him casually,
but bow to him,...

52
00:05:09,509 --> 00:05:12,637
and address him respectfully, come.

53
00:05:28,695 --> 00:05:36,363
When kids grow, their place is not
at one's feet. lt's in one's heart.

54
00:05:38,404 --> 00:05:46,368
l've come here after 18 years today.
Just to embrace you, son.

55
00:05:59,425 --> 00:06:01,552
l don't commit a faux pas, did l?

56
00:06:01,828 --> 00:06:04,991
No. You just reminded him
of your father.

57
00:06:05,431 --> 00:06:09,731
And the proud local men and women
don't let their tears be seen.

58
00:06:10,436 --> 00:06:12,927
Come, l'll show you your room.

