''These moments...''

102
00:14:00,906 --> 00:14:03,272
What's the matter with you?

103
00:14:04,076 --> 00:14:05,668
Nothing.

104
00:14:06,178 --> 00:14:10,308
Do you remember that small boy
who used to tell me everything?

105
00:14:10,583 --> 00:14:11,880
There's nothing to tell.

106
00:14:12,084 --> 00:14:14,609
Then why are you sitting
in the dark like this?

107
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:18,481
l just thought somebody
would put the light on...

108
00:14:18,924 --> 00:14:22,485
And suppose l hadn't, would you
have gone on sitting? Anyway...

109
00:14:22,928 --> 00:14:25,590
you have to go to a dinner
at Mr. Thakur, remember?

110
00:14:25,931 --> 00:14:27,899
l'm not in the mood.

111
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:31,565
lt's you who is invited,
not your mood.

112
00:14:32,004 --> 00:14:33,699
You'll have to go. Come on.

113
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:43,640
Come my son, may you live long.

114
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:49,078
l can't tell you how happy l am
to see you here.

115
00:15:15,981 --> 00:15:17,608
What happened?

116
00:15:17,917 --> 00:15:19,407
Son is it burning too much?

117
00:15:20,986 --> 00:15:22,749
lt's nothing serious.

118
00:15:22,988 --> 00:15:28,949
You're great! lf l was in your shoes,
l'd have screamed this place down.

119
00:15:29,662 --> 00:15:33,291
What's the fun in burning
without making a noise?

120
00:15:33,999 --> 00:15:36,467
You know my name?

121
00:15:39,171 --> 00:15:42,470
See what he's asking?

122
00:15:43,008 --> 00:15:47,468
Whether you know us or not,
everybody out here knows you.

123
00:15:48,180 --> 00:15:50,978
You're his Lordship from London.
And who am l?

124
00:15:52,017 --> 00:15:53,985
l'm Pallavi.
- What are you...

125
00:15:54,353 --> 00:15:57,584
And this uncle of yours,
l'm his only daughter.

126
00:15:58,023 --> 00:16:03,757
Now don't say you're happy to meet me,
for it's all said and done.

127
00:16:05,464 --> 00:16:07,329
You really made me wait.

128
00:16:09,101 --> 00:16:12,730
Now he'll say,
he had a telephone call.

129
00:16:13,339 --> 00:16:16,001
Sorry, but l got a call.

130
00:16:18,544 --> 00:16:22,173
Just as l was through with that,
l got another call.

131
00:16:23,382 --> 00:16:26,010
Just as l finished,
l got a call from the S.P.

132
00:16:27,753 --> 00:16:31,814
l'm fed up with this telephone.
l think l'll have my line cut.

133
00:16:32,491 --> 00:16:36,757
l'm really fed up with all this.
l'm thinking of having it disconnected.

134
00:16:38,597 --> 00:16:41,828
He's a first class liar!
He's always like this.

135
00:16:43,068 --> 00:16:47,027
And the funniest part is, everyone
knows he has no telephone!

