''lt's Radha you always tease''

152
00:19:37,509 --> 00:19:41,605
''She's the one you love''

153
00:19:42,014 --> 00:19:45,882
''Why have you doused
those colours on me?''

154
00:19:46,351 --> 00:19:52,221
''For l am only a milkmaid...
l'm not your Radha''

155
00:19:52,858 --> 00:19:56,624
''Do not tease me, O Krishna''

156
00:19:57,262 --> 00:20:02,962
''l'm only a milkmaid...
l'm not your Radha''

157
00:20:03,669 --> 00:20:07,628
''Do not tease me, O Krishna''

158
00:20:16,915 --> 00:20:18,780
Greetings.
- Bless you, son.

159
00:20:23,522 --> 00:20:25,490
Please have this.

160
00:20:27,659 --> 00:20:29,752
ls this the way to
accept a blessing?

161
00:20:29,995 --> 00:20:31,963
Come on, bow to me first.

162
00:20:34,199 --> 00:20:36,064
l know my name, Papa.

163
00:20:36,602 --> 00:20:40,504
Come on, bow to me.
- How can he do that?

164
00:20:41,573 --> 00:20:45,669
Why? Has he hurt his spine?
And l'm elder to him too.

165
00:20:46,278 --> 00:20:49,179
And what are you gawking at?
Come on, bow to me.

166
00:20:49,815 --> 00:20:51,442
Enough, my child.

167
00:20:51,884 --> 00:20:53,852
Okay, cup your hand please.

168
00:20:54,553 --> 00:20:56,180
The right one.

169
00:20:58,223 --> 00:21:00,191
Better you open your mouth!

170
00:21:01,426 --> 00:21:05,522
What are you looking at him for?
Forgot your mouth at home? Open it.

171
00:21:15,574 --> 00:21:17,633
You couldn't have had your breakfast?
- No.

172
00:21:17,910 --> 00:21:20,105
So have it with me.
- Daija won't forgive me, if l do.

173
00:21:20,345 --> 00:21:22,040
She won't mind if it's with me.

174
00:21:22,247 --> 00:21:24,579
He must have had all his
favorite dishes made.

175
00:21:25,350 --> 00:21:26,612
''Spicy Bread''

176
00:21:28,086 --> 00:21:31,055
My mouth's watering, dad...
l'm having my breakfast at his place.

177
00:21:31,690 --> 00:21:34,921
You go ahead and get it all ready.
l'll join you there a little later.

178
00:21:44,536 --> 00:21:47,130
l feel like having breakfast
on the terrace.

179
00:21:47,472 --> 00:21:49,997
Terrace? But it's cloudy today.

180
00:21:50,542 --> 00:21:54,342
That's wonderful! You keep it ready.
l'll just join you.

181
00:21:55,047 --> 00:21:57,015
lf it starts raining,
how will you eat?

182
00:21:57,382 --> 00:21:59,213
You'll just get wet
for nothing.

183
00:22:01,386 --> 00:22:07,086
A superb breakfast. All these tasty
things and the rain falling...

184
00:22:08,393 --> 00:22:11,362
Daija can really cook well.
- Here, have this...

185
00:22:12,397 --> 00:22:14,763
l can eat by myself now.
l've grown up.

186
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:18,697
Everybody grows up.
But no one outgrows one's elders.

187
00:22:20,672 --> 00:22:24,108
No dear, he has
really grown up now.

188
00:22:25,410 --> 00:22:29,710
You have grown big, Sir.
lt's my hands that are small.

189
00:22:31,483 --> 00:22:33,951
Your hand is bigger than the sky.

190
00:22:41,760 --> 00:22:44,160
You haven't seen Rajasthan,
have you?

191
00:22:44,429 --> 00:22:47,796
Daija, never showed it to me.
- How could l?

192
00:22:48,133 --> 00:22:49,760
lt's his first visit here.

193
00:22:50,135 --> 00:22:52,399
Then l'll make it
unforgettable for him.

194
00:22:52,804 --> 00:22:57,207
l'll show him around and
get him stuck on to it,...

195
00:22:57,676 --> 00:22:59,644
like glue on an envelope!

196
00:23:00,012 --> 00:23:03,243
Anyway, it's a wet day today.
We'll make it tomorrow. Okay?

197
00:23:04,483 --> 00:23:06,781
There's a man from
your house, Madam.

198
00:23:08,453 --> 00:23:10,421
l'll take your leave then.
Be ready tomorrow, Viren.

199
00:23:10,789 --> 00:23:13,087
Let the rain stop, my dear.
- lt's okay.

200
00:23:13,458 --> 00:23:15,085
Be ready, Viren.

201
00:23:18,864 --> 00:23:22,425
ls she the reason why you're so lost
in your thoughts these days?

202
00:23:25,470 --> 00:23:26,835
Yes.

203
00:23:27,639 --> 00:23:30,437
But she's older than you.

204
00:23:31,943 --> 00:23:35,845
So what? l'm also younger to her.
lt's quits.

205
00:23:37,482 --> 00:23:41,009
But such things are not
accepted in this country.

206
00:23:42,220 --> 00:23:44,586
Does she love you just as much?

207
00:23:46,491 --> 00:23:48,459
l don't know.

208
00:23:48,927 --> 00:23:50,895
But you must know.

209
00:23:51,697 --> 00:23:53,665
l'll ask her then.

210
00:24:03,575 --> 00:24:06,203
What's this?
- Pallavi has sent it for you.

211
00:24:06,511 --> 00:24:07,876
For me?

212
00:24:08,513 --> 00:24:10,276
A letter too?

213
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:18,221
With due regards, to
His Lordship of London.

214
00:24:19,358 --> 00:24:22,327
You must have seen such a dress
in the old portraits.

215
00:24:22,928 --> 00:24:25,488
But this is the real attire
of our ancestors.

216
00:24:26,531 --> 00:24:30,490
Play the Rajput just for today,
else you'll look like a tourist.

217
00:24:31,203 --> 00:24:34,297
And Rajasthan will not be
one with you.

218
00:24:43,415 --> 00:24:47,215
l'll look a fool in this!
- Your ancestors didn't!

219
00:24:47,552 --> 00:24:49,247
But l'm not an ancestor.

220
00:24:49,588 --> 00:24:54,321
But why tell me all this?
Return it. You can explain it to her.

221
00:24:54,860 --> 00:24:57,158
No. l'll wear it.

222
00:25:12,277 --> 00:25:15,906
l will come downstairs only if
you shut your eyes, Daija.

223
00:25:16,581 --> 00:25:17,878
All right.

224
00:25:18,316 --> 00:25:23,549
You must promise not to laugh at me.
- l promise. l will not laugh.

225
00:25:23,989 --> 00:25:25,957
Even if l feel like it.

226
00:25:40,439 --> 00:25:42,907
You promised you wouldn't laugh!

227
00:25:43,608 --> 00:25:45,576
Didn't l say l'd look mad?
l'm not going!

228
00:25:45,744 --> 00:25:49,703
No... you don't look mad at all.
You look handsome.

229
00:25:50,215 --> 00:25:52,445
Hurry up and leave.
They must be awaiting you.

230
00:25:52,684 --> 00:25:53,446
Go on.

231
00:25:53,618 --> 00:25:56,246
Do l look good?
- Very good.

232
00:26:07,632 --> 00:26:10,396
Greetings, sir.
- Greetings. May we leave?

233
00:26:11,436 --> 00:26:13,404
Have you brought the car?
- No, sir.

234
00:26:13,638 --> 00:26:16,334
ln that case, l'll take my car.
- No, sir.

235
00:26:16,875 --> 00:26:18,775
No? How will go?

236
00:26:19,044 --> 00:26:21,012
l've brought a camel, sir.
- A camel!

237
00:26:38,563 --> 00:26:39,962
Go on.

238
00:26:42,667 --> 00:26:44,635
Are you okay, sir?

239
00:27:05,690 --> 00:27:07,658
Make it stand.

240
00:27:09,694 --> 00:27:11,662
Steady...

241
00:27:40,892 --> 00:27:42,484
Nothing's going to happen.

