269
00:35:19,884 --> 00:35:23,411
This is Salamat Ali, Sir.
- Yes, go on.

270
00:35:24,055 --> 00:35:26,546
l'm sorry, but we have
lost the case, Sir.

271
00:35:27,191 --> 00:35:32,959
What? We lost the case?
But how? You said...

272
00:35:33,398 --> 00:35:36,561
l tried my best, Sir, but...

273
00:35:36,934 --> 00:35:40,893
But your best wasn't enough.

274
00:35:43,307 --> 00:35:48,176
You just lost a case,
but l've lost everything.

275
00:35:50,281 --> 00:35:56,186
My wealth, this mansion,
everything....

276
00:36:07,231 --> 00:36:10,200
What's happened?
- Nothing, my dear.

277
00:36:10,902 --> 00:36:14,861
l'll call the doctor.
You wait here, Viren, l'll just come.

278
00:36:17,842 --> 00:36:22,006
Please sit.
l want to talk to you.

279
00:36:24,248 --> 00:36:26,944
Nobody knows, except me.

280
00:36:29,253 --> 00:36:36,716
l had a case against my step-brother,
concerning our property.

281
00:36:38,396 --> 00:36:42,230
Today the court has
ruled against me.

282
00:36:45,269 --> 00:36:48,238
l'm not bothered about myself
- You'll be fine, Sir.

283
00:36:48,606 --> 00:36:53,236
Pallavi will just die,
if she gets to hear of it.

284
00:36:56,280 --> 00:36:59,977
Look after her.
Explain it to her.

285
00:37:00,718 --> 00:37:05,246
l can't keep her to
anybody else's care.

286
00:37:05,623 --> 00:37:07,386
Nothing will happen...

287
00:37:08,292 --> 00:37:10,021
l've sent for the doctor.

288
00:37:10,294 --> 00:37:12,854
Come dear;
l want to tell you something.

289
00:37:15,967 --> 00:37:19,664
Whatever l'm telling you...
- Don't talk, Papa...

290
00:37:20,304 --> 00:37:23,273
l've explained it to Viren here.

291
00:37:27,111 --> 00:37:32,879
l've entrusted your responsibility
in his hands.

292
00:37:33,317 --> 00:37:34,875
What do you mean?

293
00:37:35,119 --> 00:37:37,849
Trust him, child.

294
00:37:38,322 --> 00:37:41,291
Please rest now.
Don't talk.

295
00:38:19,363 --> 00:38:25,734
l'm very worried about her.
She hasn't eaten for the past 2 days.

296
00:38:27,371 --> 00:38:30,898
She's like a stone, she won't talk
neither will she listen.

297
00:38:32,376 --> 00:38:34,344
Please do something.

298
00:39:07,812 --> 00:39:13,546
Where had you been?
l was awaiting you for ages!

299
00:40:35,499 --> 00:40:39,196
Cry, dear...
Go ahead and cry.

300
00:40:46,977 --> 00:40:48,945
What's this?

301
00:40:52,683 --> 00:40:59,213
l didn't know my eyes
held so many tears.

302
00:40:59,924 --> 00:41:02,484
Your father mustn't be
liking you cry like this.

303
00:41:03,594 --> 00:41:08,657
l'm not used to living without him.
What shall l do?

304
00:41:09,066 --> 00:41:13,025
Face the facts, and learn
to live without him.

305
00:41:18,542 --> 00:41:20,510
But how did this happen?

306
00:41:21,212 --> 00:41:24,010
l don't know. lt was all so sudden.

307
00:41:25,883 --> 00:41:31,048
But whatever he had to tell,
he told Viren.

308
00:41:32,556 --> 00:41:34,524
Who's he?

309
00:41:35,559 --> 00:41:38,027
The son of our neighbour.

310
00:41:38,963 --> 00:41:40,931
The one who was here yesterday?

311
00:41:42,566 --> 00:41:45,535
Will you listen to something
l have to say, Viren?

312
00:41:46,570 --> 00:41:50,267
Why ask? Have l ever refused
to obey you?

313
00:41:51,375 --> 00:41:55,277
ln that case, you must return
to London today itself.

314
00:41:58,249 --> 00:42:00,217
You're being unfair, Daija.

315
00:42:00,584 --> 00:42:03,883
You wouldn't let me return,
when l wanted to.

316
00:42:04,922 --> 00:42:07,891
And now that l don't want to leave,
you're asking me to go away.

317
00:42:08,592 --> 00:42:10,059
l have promised her father.

318
00:42:12,596 --> 00:42:15,087
Mr. Siddharth is here
to see his Lordship.

319
00:42:17,001 --> 00:42:18,969
Tell him that l'll be there.

320
00:42:46,630 --> 00:42:49,258
Everything is well
over there, l hope?

321
00:42:50,067 --> 00:42:51,864
Can't really say, your Lordship.

322
00:42:52,436 --> 00:42:54,597
Call me Vir, Mr. Bhatnagar.

323
00:42:54,839 --> 00:42:58,798
That also sounds very formal.
Call me Siddharth.

324
00:43:04,014 --> 00:43:07,415
l don't know whether Pallavi
has mentioned me to you before.

325
00:43:07,985 --> 00:43:09,612
No. Nothing.

326
00:43:13,224 --> 00:43:14,919
We love each other...

327
00:43:20,664 --> 00:43:25,033
But my family background
is not as colourful as yours.

328
00:43:25,669 --> 00:43:27,637
Does that make any difference?

329
00:43:27,771 --> 00:43:32,435
Not to me, and maybe even you.
But her father was very orthodox.

330
00:43:32,843 --> 00:43:35,141
lt was very important to him.

331
00:43:36,680 --> 00:43:40,377
Let alone a background,
l don't even have a family!

332
00:43:41,785 --> 00:43:43,650
But then, your name...

333
00:43:46,290 --> 00:43:50,659
l'm told l was found on a street
and brought up in an orphanage.

334
00:43:51,695 --> 00:43:53,663
When it was time for me
to go to school...

335
00:43:53,831 --> 00:43:55,321
a father's name was essential.

336
00:43:55,699 --> 00:44:00,659
The manager liked me a lot,
so he put his own name for me.

337
00:44:01,705 --> 00:44:06,074
l was a good student, so l won
scholarships and continued to study.

338
00:44:07,244 --> 00:44:12,682
This way, an orphan became an
officer in the Air-Force...

339
00:44:13,717 --> 00:44:16,413
and at an Air-Force function,
l met Pallavi.

340
00:44:19,123 --> 00:44:21,421
l was very scared
of my feelings for her.

341
00:44:22,026 --> 00:44:26,486
But she's a special girl -
said it made no difference to her.

342
00:44:27,731 --> 00:44:30,291
And that she'd managed her father.

343
00:44:31,068 --> 00:44:36,700
He's no more, so l thought
why get married here?

344
00:44:38,909 --> 00:44:42,208
May l take her with me?
We'll get married there.

345
00:44:47,751 --> 00:44:51,312
lf you don't mind, we'd prefer
that she weds here.

346
00:44:51,755 --> 00:44:55,054
And the bridal-couple leave
her ancestral home together.

347
00:45:00,764 --> 00:45:02,732
Have you spoken to her
about the wedding?

348
00:45:02,933 --> 00:45:07,199
l thought l'd talk to Viren
and then he'd convince her..

349
00:45:08,172 --> 00:45:11,733
Don't worry about that
l'll talk to her myself.

350
00:45:22,786 --> 00:45:25,482
This is Salamat Ali speaking.

351
00:45:25,856 --> 00:45:26,754
Yes?

352
00:45:26,957 --> 00:45:32,554
l've spoken to them, like you asked.
But they are very adamant.

353
00:45:33,030 --> 00:45:36,090
Bring them to me.
l know how to deal with such lot.

354
00:45:42,539 --> 00:45:43,767
Whose phone was it?

355
00:45:46,210 --> 00:45:50,510
Give me a list of your invitees.
l'll invite them all.

356
00:45:51,315 --> 00:45:54,580
There'll be just two from my side.
Daija and yourself.

357
00:45:56,820 --> 00:45:58,447
l'll go now.

358
00:46:12,836 --> 00:46:15,202
l didn't show him my feelings,
did l?

359
00:46:15,839 --> 00:46:17,466
No, son.

360
00:46:19,109 --> 00:46:24,604
This is the mother of the deceased
and they are his...

361
00:46:24,848 --> 00:46:26,816
Step-brothers. My sons.

362
00:46:28,185 --> 00:46:30,813
You know what l want.

363
00:46:31,255 --> 00:46:34,486
How will we know what
exactly you want?

364
00:46:35,359 --> 00:46:40,228
l don't want the result of this case
disclosed to the family here.

365
00:46:40,631 --> 00:46:45,568
Pallavi will have to be told.
She has to vacate the house.

366
00:46:46,236 --> 00:46:51,196
We're sorry that he died
just after hearing the news.

367
00:46:51,675 --> 00:46:54,838
We didn't have the pleasure
of throwing him out physically..

368
00:46:55,145 --> 00:46:56,840
But this bitch...

369
00:46:58,382 --> 00:47:05,185
lf you say anything vile against them,
l'll pull your tongue out.

370
00:47:05,889 --> 00:47:07,857
Now listen to me.

371
00:47:08,392 --> 00:47:10,587
Till she leaves the house
with her husband,...

372
00:47:10,894 --> 00:47:14,853
you are to stay away from here.

373
00:47:15,332 --> 00:47:19,200
What will you give us for that?
- What's your price?

374
00:47:19,903 --> 00:47:22,531
When will she leave?
- Next week.

375
00:47:23,040 --> 00:47:25,270
That means 6 days from now.

376
00:47:25,909 --> 00:47:28,400
That makes it 600,000.

377
00:47:28,912 --> 00:47:31,881
And one more extra for the slap
you gave me.

378
00:47:40,924 --> 00:47:42,892
Give them a cheque of one million.

379
00:47:51,268 --> 00:47:53,702
Today all my efforts
have been worth it.

380
00:47:54,271 --> 00:47:56,705
Today you've really matured.

381
00:47:58,008 --> 00:48:00,033
Today l feel like addressing you
with your Title.

382
00:48:04,948 --> 00:48:06,916
l have arrived.

383
00:48:18,128 --> 00:48:20,289
How are you?
- Losing some hair...

384
00:48:25,135 --> 00:48:26,432
How come you're here?

385
00:48:26,570 --> 00:48:28,834
Then would there be a wedding
without me?

386
00:48:37,214 --> 00:48:39,375
There's something l wanted
to discuss with you.

387
00:48:41,585 --> 00:48:42,677
One moment...

388
00:48:43,821 --> 00:48:45,288
Greetings!

389
00:48:45,556 --> 00:48:49,720
My name is Prem.
l'm Viren's childhood friend.

390
00:48:50,127 --> 00:48:53,028
When l was 7 year's old...

391
00:48:54,498 --> 00:48:55,897
Greetings- Greetings.

392
00:49:08,145 --> 00:49:10,909
The girl's superb. When are you getting
married my dear...

393
00:49:11,114 --> 00:49:14,641
You've just come. Have a wash,
then we'll chat...

394
00:49:14,852 --> 00:49:22,349
What a girl, What a choice...

395
00:49:24,561 --> 00:49:28,998
l admit she's so lovely.
lt won't be easy to forget her.

396
00:49:30,033 --> 00:49:32,661
But you should have told her
of your feelings, at least once.

397
00:49:33,036 --> 00:49:36,528
What difference would that have made?
She'd have loved her guy anyway.

398
00:49:37,207 --> 00:49:39,107
Well, it's not the end
of the world!

399
00:49:39,243 --> 00:49:41,006
Who knows?

400
00:49:42,045 --> 00:49:43,171
But you....

401
00:49:43,447 --> 00:49:45,677
There are no ''ifs''
and ''buts'' in love.

402
00:49:47,384 --> 00:49:53,755
And before loving her, l hadn't put
a condition that she loves me too.

403
00:49:55,392 --> 00:50:02,355
She loved Siddharth, she'll be
happy with him. That's all l want.

404
00:50:06,069 --> 00:50:08,367
May God save you
from the evil-eye.

405
00:50:08,739 --> 00:50:14,200
You always were beautiful. But never
as beautiful as you look today.

406
00:50:16,146 --> 00:50:18,444
l miss my father very much.

407
00:50:20,083 --> 00:50:22,643
That you will, all your life.

408
00:50:23,387 --> 00:50:27,756
He always said he'd go
as ''dowry'' with you.

409
00:50:28,425 --> 00:50:30,791
Now his memories are your dowry.

410
00:50:31,461 --> 00:50:33,429
No, don't cry.

411
00:50:35,165 --> 00:50:38,066
May God give you
a long happy life.

412
00:50:41,438 --> 00:50:44,271
What's wrong with Viren?
He hasn't met me for days.

413
00:50:46,109 --> 00:50:53,413
He's very busy with the preparations.
He's your care-taker now.

414
00:50:55,185 --> 00:50:59,087
Tell him that l won't leave
without meeting him.

415
00:50:59,690 --> 00:51:02,090
lf l see him,
l'll give him your message.

416
00:51:07,297 --> 00:51:10,095
''This kurta that's
made of muslin...''

417
00:51:10,701 --> 00:51:13,135
''come dressed in it''

418
00:51:14,137 --> 00:51:22,101
''l await you at the door.
Come dressed in a muslin kurta...''

419
00:51:25,148 --> 00:51:28,117
l was told you were
asking for me...

420
00:51:42,165 --> 00:51:45,862
l don't know whether my father
was happy with my choice.

421
00:51:47,270 --> 00:51:53,869
But since l'm in your charge...
tell me, do you approve?

422
00:51:55,612 --> 00:51:57,341
Why not?

423
00:51:59,082 --> 00:52:01,448
Questions are not answered
by counter questioning.

424
00:52:03,754 --> 00:52:05,221
Are you happy?

425
00:52:06,757 --> 00:52:07,985
Yes.

426
00:52:08,792 --> 00:52:10,760
Then l am too.

427
00:52:14,431 --> 00:52:18,765
l've been very bad to you.
l've really harassed you.

428
00:52:20,203 --> 00:52:21,670
What nonsense!

429
00:52:22,205 --> 00:52:25,174
You're very nice,
very decent.

430
00:52:28,545 --> 00:52:31,776
lf l can ever be of help,
write to me.

431
00:52:36,486 --> 00:52:38,181
Can l?

432
00:52:39,556 --> 00:52:40,648
Go on.

433
00:52:43,627 --> 00:52:47,757
Can l call you by
your first name?

434
00:52:51,234 --> 00:52:55,933
Come, my dear. Everybody is waiting.
You too Viren.

435
00:53:34,778 --> 00:53:45,120
''These moments, these memories,
l shall cherish for years to come''

436
00:53:45,722 --> 00:53:56,394
''Should the seasons change,
l will beg for them''

437
00:53:57,300 --> 00:54:08,143
''These moments, these memories,
l shall cherish for years to come''

438
00:54:08,678 --> 00:54:19,646
''Should the seasons change,
l will appeal for them''

439
00:54:20,724 --> 00:54:26,424
''l will cherish for years...''

440
00:54:42,746 --> 00:54:44,543
May you live long.

441
00:54:50,053 --> 00:54:59,894
Whenever you come, stay here a while.
Nobody should say the house is empty.

442
00:55:00,363 --> 00:55:03,332
No, don't worry about that.

443
00:55:03,700 --> 00:55:06,328
We'll look after the house
for you now.

444
00:55:08,371 --> 00:55:10,737
What are these people doing here?

445
00:55:11,374 --> 00:55:16,141
Tell her, Sir. She's asking
what are we doing here?

446
00:55:17,714 --> 00:55:22,947
This is ours now. We were quiet,
because of Viren

447
00:55:23,386 --> 00:55:26,150
Else we'd have thrown you out
six days ago.

448
00:55:26,489 --> 00:55:28,582
Can't you people be polite?

449
00:55:28,959 --> 00:55:32,156
Who is this guy? ls he trying
to teach us to be polite?

450
00:55:32,729 --> 00:55:35,755
Don't ever think it's only the Rajputs
who are self-respecting

451
00:55:36,399 --> 00:55:39,766
Every decent man can kill
and die for his self-respect

452
00:55:40,070 --> 00:55:43,096
lf you say another word,
there'll be a death here.

453
00:55:44,007 --> 00:55:46,976
Whose death?
- Either yours, or mine.

454
00:55:48,812 --> 00:55:51,372
No. This is not the
time to keep quiet.

455
00:55:52,415 --> 00:55:56,374
You people had said,
you'd come tomorrow.

456
00:55:56,853 --> 00:56:02,189
You've got it wrong. We were paid
a million to keep away till today.

457
00:56:04,427 --> 00:56:08,386
What's all this about?
What time limit? Which million?

458
00:56:10,433 --> 00:56:13,732
Throw these people
out of our property.

459
00:56:15,438 --> 00:56:18,066
This house, this land,
is all ours now.

460
00:56:18,508 --> 00:56:20,738
Your father had lost the case...

461
00:56:23,880 --> 00:56:30,843
Yes, Viren wanted you to leave happily
before they claimed it all.

462
00:56:31,521 --> 00:56:34,081
That's why he had to buy
some time from them.

463
00:56:35,458 --> 00:56:43,160
Papa died, the mansion is not mine.
l've become all alone now.

464
00:56:43,900 --> 00:56:49,861
God forbid! Why should you feel alone?
You have your husband with you.

465
00:56:57,747 --> 00:57:02,878
l cried so much against these walls.
Such insult to those tears.

466
00:57:03,787 --> 00:57:06,255
l'll never forgive Viren for this.

467
00:57:07,490 --> 00:57:11,950
That's your personal opinion,
but he did his duty.

468
00:57:12,729 --> 00:57:17,462
We both are indebted to him.
And it's a debt we can never repay.

469
00:57:19,502 --> 00:57:22,471
Just take me away from here.

470
00:57:24,674 --> 00:57:30,476
Bless you, dear.
But don't misunderstand Viren.

471
00:57:31,047 --> 00:57:37,145
There's no question about that.
Now l know why he didn't wait for you.

472
00:57:38,621 --> 00:57:45,083
He didn't want to face this moment.
ln his place, l'd have done the same.

473
00:57:46,529 --> 00:57:50,295
No work is done without contacts
these days, especially plane-bookings.

474
00:57:50,867 --> 00:57:53,097
Your seats are confirmed.

475
00:57:53,536 --> 00:57:56,096
Who are those other tickets for?
- For you.

476
00:57:56,539 --> 00:57:58,507
And the former one?
- For me.

477
